The paper deals with the problem of counting nodes in a distributed network, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The network is assumed to be dynamic, which suggests the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The problem of counting is a fundamental task in distributed computing, which also suggests the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper presents a protocol for solving the problem, which suggests the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of the protocol, which suggests the category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
